---
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <meta charset="UTF-8" />
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
        <title>Projects - Graham Tomori</title>
    </head>

    <body class="font-sans bg-gray-50">
        <!-- Navbar -->
        <nav class="fixed top-0 left-0 w-full bg-white shadow z-50">
            <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-4 flex justify-between items-center">
                <a href="/" class="text-xl font-bold">Graham Tomori</a>
                <div class="space-x-6">
                    <a href="/" class="hover:text-blue-500">Home</a>
                    <a href="/about" class="hover:text-blue-500">About</a>
                    <a href="/projects" class="hover:text-blue-500 font-semibold">Projects</a>
                    <a href="/contact" class="hover:text-blue-500">Contact</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </nav>

        <!-- Projects Section -->
        <section class="min-h-screen flex items-center justify-center bg-gradient-to-r from-black-500 to-white-600 pt-24">
            <div class="max-w-4xl bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg p-10 text-gray-800">
                <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-6 text-center">Projects</h1>
                <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-4">
                    Here are some of the projects I’ve been working on recently. These include web development, research, and initiatives focused on
                    international business and nation development.
                </p>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
                    <li><strong>MOCKIMFPROJECT</strong> – A think tank simulation exploring global economics and policy.</li>
                    <li><strong>Personal Website</strong> – This site, built with Astro + Tailwind.</li>
                    <li><strong>Development Case Studies</strong> – Research into rebuilding post-conflict nations.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>
    </body>
</html>
